nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell killing, the process in which a cell brings about the death of another cell, either in the same or a different organism.

nodes.name: regulation of complement-dependent cytotoxicity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of complement-dependent cytotoxicity.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular component biogenesis
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular component biogenesis, a process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a cellular component.

nodes.name: regulation of inclusion body assembly
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of inclusion body assembly. Inclusion body assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an inclusion body.

nodes.name: regulation of neurofibrillary tangle assembly
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurofibrillary tangle assembly.

nodes.name: regulation of ribosome biogenesis
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of ribosome biogenesis. Ribosome biogenesis is the cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

nodes.name: modulation by symbiont of host cellular process
nodes.description: Any process in which a symbiont organism modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any process that is carried out at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell, in its host organism.

nodes.name: modulation by virus of host process
nodes.description: The process in which a virus effects a change in the processes and activities of its host organism.

nodes.name: induction by virus of host cell-cell fusion
nodes.description: The process of syncytia-forming cell-cell fusion, caused by a virus.

nodes.name: regulation of cell adhesion
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of attachment of a cell to another cell or to the extracellular matrix.

nodes.name: regulation of cell adhesion mediated by integrin
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of cell adhesion mediated by integrin.

nodes.name: regulation of cell cycle
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of progression through the cell cycle.

nodes.name: regulation of cell cycle process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

nodes.name: regulation of nuclear cell cycle DNA replication
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of The DNA-dependent DNA replication that occurs in the nucleus of eukaryotic organisms as part of the cell cycle.

nodes.name: regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity involved in G2/M transition of mitotic cell cycle
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity contributing to the G2/M transition of the cell cycle.

nodes.name: regulation of cell death
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate or frequency of cell death. Cell death is the specific activation or halting of processes within a cell so that its vital functions markedly cease, rather than simply deteriorating gradually over time, which culminates in cell death.

nodes.name: regulation of programmed cell death
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death, cell death resulting from activation of endogenous cellular processes.

nodes.name: regulation of apoptotic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptotic process.

nodes.name: regulation of apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular component movement
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the movement of a cellular component.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cellular component movement
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the movement of a cellular component.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cell motility
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell motility.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cell migration
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell migration.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular component organization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

nodes.name: regulation of formation of translation preinitiation complex
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of formation of translation preinitiation complex.

nodes.name: regulation of organelle organization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

nodes.name: regulation of mitochondrion organization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a mitochondrion.

nodes.name: regulation of protein targeting to mitochondrion
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein targeting to mitochondrion.

nodes.name: regulation of protein processing involved in protein targeting to mitochondrion
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein processing involved in protein targeting to mitochondrion.

nodes.name: regulation of release of cytochrome c from mitochondria
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of release of cytochrome c from mitochondria, the process in which cytochrome c is enabled to move from the mitochondrial intermembrane space into the cytosol, which is an early step in apoptosis and leads to caspase activation.

nodes.name: regulation of protein complex assembly
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex assembly.

nodes.name: regulation of proteasome assembly
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a mature, active proteasome complex.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular localization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity is transported to, or maintained in a specific location within or in the membrane of a cell.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular protein localization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular protein localization. Cellular protein localization is any process in which a protein is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location and encompasses movement within the cell, from within the cell to the cell surface, or from one location to another at the surface of a cell.

nodes.name: regulation of intracellular protein transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

nodes.name: regulation of protein targeting
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein targeting.

nodes.name: regulation of protein import into nucleus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of movement of proteins from the cytoplasm to the nucleus.

nodes.name: regulation of transcription factor import into nucleus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the movement of a transcription factor from the cytoplasm to the nucleus.

nodes.name: regulation of NF-kappaB import into nucleus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the transfer of NF-kappaB, a transcription factor for eukaryotic RNA polymerase II promoters, from the cytoplasm into the nucleus, across the nuclear membrane.

nodes.name: regulation of viral process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of the viral life cycle, the set of processes by which a virus reproduces and spreads among hosts.

nodes.name: regulation of circadian rhythm
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a circadian rhythm. A circadian rhythm is a biological process in an organism that recurs with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

nodes.name: positive regulation of circadian rhythm
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a circadian rhythm behavior.

nodes.name: regulation of developmental process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of development, the biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a multicellular organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote, or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult).

nodes.name: regulation of cell differentiation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation, the process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and functional features.

nodes.name: regulation of cell fate commitment
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell fate commitment. Cell fate commitment is the commitment of cells to specific cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into particular kinds of cells. Positional information is established through protein signals that emanate from a localized source within a cell (the initial one-cell zygote) or within a developmental field.

nodes.name: regulation of cell fate specification
nodes.description: Any process that mediates the adoption of a specific fate by a cell.

nodes.name: activation of prostate induction by androgen receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of an androgen binding to its receptor in the urogenital sinus mesenchyme that initiates prostate induction. Prostate induction is the close range interaction of the urogenital sinus mesenchyme and the urogenital sinus epithelium that causes the cells of the urogenital sinus epithelium to change their fates and specify the development of the prostate gland.

nodes.name: regulation of myeloid cell differentiation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid cell differentiation.

nodes.name: regulation of immune system process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

nodes.name: negative regulation of immune system process
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

nodes.name: negative regulation of toll-like receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: negative regulation of toll-like receptor 9 signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of toll-like receptor 9 signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of localization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

nodes.name: regulation of protein localization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

nodes.name: regulation of establishment of protein localization
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein to a specific location.

nodes.name: regulation of protein transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: regulation of protein secretion
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a protein from a cell.

nodes.name: negative regulation of protein secretion
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a protein from a cell.

nodes.name: negative regulation of matrix metallopeptidase secretion
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of matrix metallopeptidase secretion.

nodes.name: positive regulation of protein secretion
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a protein from a cell.

nodes.name: positive regulation of matrix metallopeptidase secretion
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of matrix metallopeptidase secretion.

nodes.name: regulation of insulin secretion
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin.

nodes.name: regulation of insulin secretion involved in cellular response to glucose stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin that contributes to the response of a cell to glucose.

nodes.name: regulation of matrix metallopeptidase secretion
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of matrix metallopeptidase secretion.

nodes.name: regulation of transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: regulation of ion transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of charged atoms or small charged molecules into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: regulation of anion transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of anions, atoms or small molecules with a net negative charge into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: regulation of chloride transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chloride transport.

nodes.name: regulation of metal ion transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of metal ion transport. Metal ion transport is the directed movement of metal ions, any metal ion with an electric charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: regulation of potassium ion transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of potassium ions (K+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: negative regulation of potassium ion transport
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of potassium ions (K+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: positive regulation of potassium ion transport
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of potassium ions (K+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

nodes.name: regulation of transmembrane transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a solute from one side of a membrane to the other.

nodes.name: regulation of ion transmembrane transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

nodes.name: regulation of cation transmembrane transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cation transmembrane transport.

nodes.name: regulation of cation channel activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cation channel activity.

nodes.name: negative regulation of cation channel activity
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cation channel activity.

nodes.name: negative regulation of calcium channel activity in other organism
nodes.description: Any process in which an organism stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a calcium channel in another organism.

nodes.name: negative regulation of voltage-gated calcium channel activity in other organism
nodes.description: Any process in which an organism stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a voltage-gated calcium channel in another organism. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

nodes.name: negative regulation of low voltage-gated calcium channel activity in other organism
nodes.description: Any process in which an organism stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of a low voltage-gated calcium channel in another organism. A low voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on low voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cation channel activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cation channel activity.

nodes.name: positive regulation of voltage-gated potassium channel activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of voltage-gated potassium channel activity.

nodes.name: regulation of potassium ion transmembrane transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of potassium ion transmembrane transport.

nodes.name: regulation of ion transmembrane transporter activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the activity of an ion transporter.

nodes.name: regulation of potassium ion transmembrane transporter activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of potassium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

nodes.name: regulation of inward rectifier potassium channel activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of inward rectifier potassium channel activity.

nodes.name: regulation of G-protein activated inward rectifier potassium channel activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of G-protein activated inward rectifier potassium channel activity.

nodes.name: regulation of protein import into mitochondrial outer membrane
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein import into mitochondrial outer membrane.

nodes.name: regulation of vesicle-mediated transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of vesicle-mediated transport, the directed movement of substances, either within a vesicle or in the vesicle membrane, into, out of or within a cell.

nodes.name: regulation of exocytosis
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of exocytosis.

nodes.name: regulation of regulated secretory pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of regulated secretory pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of leukocyte degranulation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte degranulation.

nodes.name: regulation of cytotoxic T cell degranulation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of cytotoxic T cell degranulation.

nodes.name: regulation of Golgi to plasma membrane protein transport
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the transport of proteins from the Golgi to the plasma membrane.

nodes.name: regulation of metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

nodes.name: regulation of biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances, carried out by individual cells.

nodes.name: regulation of retinoic acid biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retinoic acid biosynthetic process.

nodes.name: regulation of macromolecule biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a macromolecule, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular macromolecule biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular macromolecule biosynthetic process.

nodes.name: regulation of glycoprotein biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glycoproteins, any protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues; the glycose occurs most commonly as oligosaccharide or fairly small polysaccharide but occasionally as monosaccharide.

nodes.name: regulation of amyloid precursor protein biosynthetic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of amyloid precursor protein (APP), the precursor of beta-amyloid.

nodes.name: regulation of catabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances.

nodes.name: regulation of collagen catabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of collagen catabolism. Collagen catabolism is the proteolytic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of collagen in the extracellular matrix.

nodes.name: regulation of catalytic activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the activity of an enzyme.

nodes.name: negative regulation of catalytic activity
nodes.description: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of an enzyme.

nodes.name: negative regulation of transferase activity
nodes.description: Any process that stops or reduces the rate of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from a donor compound to an acceptor.

nodes.name: negative regulation of ubiquitin-protein transferase activity
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquitin transferase activity.

nodes.name: positive regulation of catalytic activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of an enzyme.

nodes.name: positive regulation of hydrolase activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hydrolase activity, the catalysis of the hydrolysis of various bonds.

nodes.name: positive regulation of GTPase activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a GTPase.

nodes.name: regulation of hydrolase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hydrolase activity, the catalysis of the hydrolysis of various bonds, e.g. C-O, C-N, C-C, phosphoric anhydride bonds, etc. Hydrolase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 3.

nodes.name: regulation of ATPase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate of ATP hydrolysis by an ATPase.

nodes.name: regulation of proteasome-activating ATPase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of proteasome-activating ATPase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of GTPase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate of GTP hydrolysis by a GTPase.

nodes.name: regulation of lipase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lipase activity, the hydrolysis of a lipid or phospholipid.

nodes.name: regulation of phospholipase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of phospholipase activity, the hydrolysis of a phospholipid.

nodes.name: regulation of ligase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ligase activity, the catalysis of the ligation of two substances with concomitant breaking of a diphosphate linkage, usually in a nucleoside triphosphate. Ligase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 6.

nodes.name: regulation of aminoacyl-tRNA ligase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of aminoacyl-tRNA ligase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of oxidoreductase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oxidoreductase activity, the catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction, a reversible chemical reaction in which the oxidation state of an atom or atoms within a molecule is altered. One substrate acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and becomes oxidized, while the other acts as hydrogen or electron acceptor and becomes reduced.

nodes.name: regulation of transferase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

nodes.name: regulation of kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

nodes.name: regulation of protein kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein kinase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of tau-protein kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of tau-protein kinase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of SUMO transferase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of SUMO ligase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular amide metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amides.

nodes.name: regulation of beta-amyloid formation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of beta-amyloid formation.

nodes.name: regulation of phosphorus metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphorus or compounds containing phosphorus.

nodes.name: regulation of phosphate metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphates.

nodes.name: regulation of dephosphorylation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of removal of phosphate groups from a molecule.

nodes.name: regulation of phosphorylation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups into a molecule.

nodes.name: regulation of protein phosphorylation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups into an amino acid in a protein.

nodes.name: positive regulation of protein phosphorylation
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups to amino acids within a protein.

nodes.name: positive regulation of protein kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein kinase activity.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of CDK activity.

nodes.name: regulation of peptidyl-tyrosine phosphorylation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the phosphorylation of peptidyl-tyrosine.

nodes.name: regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of macromolecule metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

nodes.name: regulation of protein metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular protein metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein, occurring at the level of an individual cell.

nodes.name: regulation of protein folding
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein folding.

nodes.name: regulation of chaperone-mediated protein folding
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chaperone-mediated protein folding.

nodes.name: regulation of protein modification process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the covalent alteration of one or more amino acid residues within a protein.

nodes.name: regulation of post-translational protein modification
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of post-translational protein modification.

nodes.name: negative regulation of post-translational protein modification
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of post-translational protein modification.

nodes.name: regulation of protein dephosphorylation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of removal of phosphate groups from a protein.

nodes.name: regulation of phosphatase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate or frequency of phosphatase activity. Phosphatases catalyze the hydrolysis of phosphoric monoesters, releasing inorganic phosphate.

nodes.name: regulation of alkaline phosphatase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of alkaline phosphatase activity, the catalysis of the reaction: an orthophosphoric monoester + H2O = an alcohol + phosphate, with an alkaline pH optimum.

nodes.name: negative regulation of alkaline phosphatase activity
nodes.description: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of alkaline phosphatase activity, the catalysis of the reaction: an orthophosphoric monoester + H2O = an alcohol + phosphate, with an alkaline pH optimum.

nodes.name: positive regulation of alkaline phosphatase activity
nodes.description: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of alkaline phosphatase activity, the catalysis of the reaction: an orthophosphoric monoester + H2O = an alcohol + phosphate, with an alkaline pH optimum.

nodes.name: regulation of phosphoprotein phosphatase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of phosphoprotein phosphatase activity, the catalysis of the hydrolysis of phosphate from a phosphoprotein.

nodes.name: regulation of protein tyrosine phosphatase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein tyrosine phosphatase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of protein modification by small protein conjugation or removal
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein modification by small protein conjugation or removal.

nodes.name: regulation of protein sumoylation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the addition of SUMO groups to a protein.

nodes.name: regulation of proteolysis
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the hydrolysis of a peptide bond or bonds within a protein.

nodes.name: regulation of peptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of peptidase activity, the hydrolysis of peptide bonds within proteins.

nodes.name: regulation of endopeptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endopeptidase activity, the endohydrolysis of peptide bonds within proteins.

nodes.name: regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity.

nodes.name: positive regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity.

nodes.name: activation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme cysteine-type endopeptidase.

nodes.name: activation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic process
nodes.description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme cysteine-type endopeptidase in the context of an apoptotic process.

nodes.name: regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the activity of a cysteine-type endopeptidase involved in apoptosis.

nodes.name: regulation of serine-type peptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of serine-type peptidase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of serine-type endopeptidase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of serine-type endopeptidase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity (deubiquitinase) activity.

nodes.name: regulation of nitrogen compound metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nitrogen or nitrogenous compounds.

nodes.name: regulation of nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
nodes.description: Any cellular process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

nodes.name: regulation of DNA metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving DNA.

nodes.name: regulation of DNA repair
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA repair.

nodes.name: regulation of nucleotide-excision repair
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nucleotide-excision repair.

nodes.name: regulation of nucleotide metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleotides.

nodes.name: regulation of NADP metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of NADP metabolic process.

nodes.name: regulation of primary metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism involving those compounds formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

nodes.name: regulation of carbohydrate metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular carbohydrate metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, extent or frequency of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, as carried out by individual cells.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular carbohydrate catabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrates, carried out by individual cells.

nodes.name: regulation of glycogen catabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glycogen.

nodes.name: regulation of glucose metabolic process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of glucose metabolism. Glucose metabolic processes are the chemical reactions and pathways involving glucose, the aldohexose gluco-hexose.

nodes.name: regulation of hexokinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hexokinase activity.

nodes.name: negative regulation of hexokinase activity
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hexokinase activity.

nodes.name: regulation of multicellular organismal process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a multicellular organismal process, the processes pertinent to the function of a multicellular organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

nodes.name: regulation of beta-amyloid clearance
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of beta-amyloid clearance.

nodes.name: regulation of system process
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system.

nodes.name: regulation of blood circulation
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood circulation.

nodes.name: regulation of heart contraction
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of heart contraction. Heart contraction is the process in which the heart decreases in volume in a characteristic way to propel blood through the body.

nodes.name: cardiac conduction
nodes.description: Transfer of an organized electrical impulse across the heart to coordinate the contraction of cardiac muscles. The process begins with generation of an action potential (in the sinoatrial node (SA) in humans) and ends with a change in the rate, frequency, or extent of the contraction of the heart muscles.

nodes.name: regulation of response to stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to a stimulus. Response to stimulus is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus.

nodes.name: regulation of cellular response to growth factor stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a growth factor stimulus.

nodes.name: regulation of response to external stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to an external stimulus.

nodes.name: regulation of defense response to bacterium
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of defense response to bacterium.

nodes.name: regulation of response to extracellular stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to an extracellular stimulus.

nodes.name: regulation of response to nutrient levels
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to nutrient levels.

nodes.name: regulation of response to stress
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to stress. Response to stress is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis, usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

nodes.name: regulation of cellular response to stress
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular response to stress. Cellular response to stress is a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

nodes.name: regulation of response to DNA damage stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of response to DNA damage stimulus.

nodes.name: regulation of response to oxidative stress
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of response to oxidative stress.

nodes.name: regulation of signaling
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling process.

nodes.name: regulation of cardiac conduction
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac conduction.

nodes.name: regulation of cell communication by electrical coupling involved in cardiac conduction
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication by electrical coupling involved in cardiac conduction.

nodes.name: regulation of signal transduction
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

nodes.name: negative regulation of signal transduction
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

nodes.name: extracellular negative regulation of signal transduction
nodes.description: Any negative regulation of signal transduction that takes place in extracellular region.

nodes.name: sequestering of extracellular ligand from receptor
nodes.description: The process of binding or confining an extracellular signaling ligand, such that the ligand is unable to bind to its cell surface receptor.

nodes.name: sequestering of TGFbeta from receptor via TGFbeta binding
nodes.description: Binding to a transforming growth factor-beta (TGFbeta) protein in the extracellular region, and inhibiting TGFbeta signaling by preventing TGFbeta from binding to its cell surface receptor.

nodes.name: positive regulation of signal transduction
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

nodes.name: positive regulation of Wnt signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of Wnt signal transduction.

nodes.name: regulation of CD40 signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signaling via the CD40 signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of cytokine-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cytokine mediated signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of chemokine-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the series of molecular events generated as a consequence of a chemokine binding to a cell surface receptor.

nodes.name: regulation of C-C chemokine receptor CCR7 signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of C-C chemokine receptor CCR7 signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of G-protein coupled receptor protein signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of G-protein coupled receptor protein signaling pathway activity.

nodes.name: regulation of adrenergic receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of an adrenergic receptor signaling pathway activity. An adrenergic receptor signaling pathway is the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of an adrenergic receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands.

nodes.name: regulation of dopamine receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a dopamine receptor signaling pathway activity. A dopamine receptor signaling pathway is the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a dopamine receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands.

nodes.name: regulation of endocannabinoid signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endocannabinoid signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of opioid receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of opioid receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of phospholipase C-activating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of phospholipase C-activating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: negative regulation of phospholipase C-activating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of phospholipase C-activating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of glutamate receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of intracellular signal transduction
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of intracellular signal transduction.

nodes.name: regulation of calcium-mediated signaling
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of calcium-mediated signaling, the process in which a cell uses calcium ions to convert an extracellular signal into a response.

nodes.name: positive regulation of calcium-mediated signaling
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of calcium-mediated signaling.

nodes.name: positive regulation of calcineurin-NFAT signaling cascade
nodes.description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signaling via the calcineurin-NFAT signaling cascade.

nodes.name: regulation of I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB signaling
nodes.description: Any process that modulates I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB signaling.

nodes.name: regulation of JAK-STAT cascade
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the JAK-STAT signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of tyrosine phosphorylation of STAT protein
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the introduction of a phosphate group to a tyrosine residue of a STAT (Signal Transducer and Activator of Transcription) protein.

nodes.name: regulation of phosphorelay signal transduction system
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction via a phosphorelay signal transduction system.

nodes.name: regulation of protein kinase C signaling
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of a series of reactions, mediated by the intracellular serine/threonine kinase protein kinase C, which occurs as a result of a single trigger reaction or compound.

nodes.name: regulation of intracellular steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of any intracellular steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: negative regulation of intracellular steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of any intracellular steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: negative regulation of intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of an intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of an intracellular estrogen receptor signaling pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of retinoic acid receptor signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retinoic acid receptor signaling pathway activity.

nodes.name: regulation of Wnt signaling pathway
nodes.description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the activity of the Wnt signal transduction pathway.

nodes.name: regulation of biological quality
nodes.description: Any process that modulates a qualitative or quantitative trait of a biological quality. A biological quality is a measurable attribute of an organism or part of an organism, such as size, mass, shape, color, etc.

nodes.name: homeostatic process
nodes.description: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state.

nodes.name: chemical homeostasis
nodes.description: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of a chemical.

nodes.name: ion homeostasis
nodes.description: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of ions within an organism or cell.

nodes.name: cation homeostasis
nodes.description: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of cations within an organism or cell.

nodes.name: monovalent inorganic cation homeostasis
nodes.description: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of monovalent inorganic cations within an organism or cell.

nodes.name: potassium ion homeostasis
nodes.description: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of potassium ions within an organism or cell.

nodes.name: cell cycle
nodes.description: The progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events. Canonically, the cell cycle comprises the replication and segregation of genetic material followed by the division of the cell, but in endocycles or syncytial cells nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division.

nodes.name: mitotic cell cycle
nodes.description: Progression through the phases of the mitotic cell cycle, the most common eukaryotic cell cycle, which canonically comprises four successive phases called G1, S, G2, and M and includes replication of the genome and the subsequent segregation of chromosomes into daughter cells. In some variant cell cycles nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division, or G1 and G2 phases may be absent.

nodes.name: cell death
nodes.description: Any biological process that results in permanent cessation of all vital functions of a cell. A cell should be considered dead when any one of the following molecular or morphological criteria is met: (1) the cell has lost the integrity of its plasma membrane; (2) the cell, including its nucleus, has undergone complete fragmentation into discrete bodies (frequently referred to as "apoptotic bodies"); and/or (3) its corpse (or its fragments) have been engulfed by an adjacent cell in vivo.

nodes.name: cell death in response to oxidative stress
nodes.description: Any biological process that results in permanent cessation of all vital functions of a cell upon exposure to an oxidative stress stimulus.

nodes.name: programmed cell death
nodes.description: A process which begins when a cell receives an internal or external signal and activates a series of biochemical events (signaling pathway). The process ends with the death of the cell.

nodes.name: host programmed cell death induced by symbiont
nodes.description: Cell death in a host resulting from activation of host endogenous cellular processes after direct or indirect interaction with a symbiont (defined as the smaller of two, or more, organisms engaged in symbiosis, a close interaction encompassing mutualism through parasitism). An example of direct interaction is contact with penetrating hyphae of a fungus; an example of indirect interaction is encountering symbiont-secreted molecules.

nodes.name: pyroptosis
nodes.description: A caspase-1-dependent cell death subroutine that is associated with the generation of pyrogenic mediators such as IL-1beta and IL-18.

nodes.name: cell killing
nodes.description: Any process in an organism that results in the killing of its own cells or those of another organism, including in some cases the death of the other organism. Killing here refers to the induction of death in one cell by another cell, not cell-autonomous death due to internal or other environmental conditions.

nodes.name: killing of cells of other organism
nodes.description: Any process in an organism that results in the killing of cells of another organism, including in some cases the death of the other organism. Killing here refers to the induction of death in one cell by another cell, not cell-autonomous death due to internal or other environmental conditions.

nodes.name: cell proliferation
nodes.description: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

nodes.name: common myeloid progenitor cell proliferation
nodes.description: The multiplication or reproduction of common myeloid progenitor cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. A common myeloid progenitor cell is a progenitor cell committed to the myeloid lineage.

nodes.name: epithelial cell proliferation
nodes.description: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. Epithelial cells make up the epithelium, the covering of internal and external surfaces of the body, including the lining of vessels and other small cavities. It consists of cells joined by small amounts of cementing substances.

nodes.name: endothelial cell proliferation
nodes.description: The multiplication or reproduction of endothelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. Endothelial cells are thin flattened cells which line the inside surfaces of body cavities, blood vessels, and lymph vessels, making up the endothelium.

nodes.name: stem cell proliferation
nodes.description: The multiplication or reproduction of stem cells, resulting in the expansion of a stem cell population. A stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

nodes.name: cellular process
nodes.description: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

nodes.name: cell wall organization or biogenesis
nodes.description: A process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cell wall.

nodes.name: cell wall organization
nodes.description: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the cell wall, the rigid or semi-rigid envelope lying outside the cell membrane of plant, fungal and most prokaryotic cells, maintaining their shape and protecting them from osmotic lysis.

nodes.name: cell wall disassembly
nodes.description: A process that results in the breakdown of the cell wall.

nodes.name: cellular component organization
nodes.description: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.

nodes.name: external encapsulating structure organization
nodes.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of external structures that lie outside the plasma membrane and surround the entire cell.

nodes.name: capsule organization
nodes.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the capsule, a protective structure surrounding some species of bacteria and fungi.

nodes.name: macromolecular complex subunit organization
nodes.description: Any process in which macromolecules aggregate, disaggregate, or are modified, resulting in the formation, disassembly, or alteration of a macromolecular complex.

nodes.name: chromatin organization
nodes.description: Any process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the physical structure of eukaryotic chromatin.

nodes.name: chromatin modification
nodes.description: The alteration of DNA, protein, or sometimes RNA, in chromatin, which may result in changing the chromatin structure.

nodes.name: chromatin remodeling
nodes.description: Dynamic structural changes to eukaryotic chromatin occurring throughout the cell division cycle. These changes range from the local changes necessary for transcriptional regulation to global changes necessary for chromosome segregation.

nodes.name: protein complex subunit organization
nodes.description: Any process in which macromolecules aggregate, disaggregate, or are modified, resulting in the formation, disassembly, or alteration of a protein complex.

nodes.name: protein complex assembly
nodes.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a protein complex.

nodes.name: integrin activation
nodes.description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of an integrin, a heterodimeric adhesion receptor formed by the non-covalent association of particular alpha and beta subunits, that lead to the increased affinity of the integrin for its extracellular ligands.

nodes.name: membrane organization
nodes.description: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a membrane. A membrane is a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

nodes.name: single-organism membrane organization
nodes.description: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a membrane, involving only one organism.

nodes.name: neuronal ion channel clustering
nodes.description: The process in which voltage-gated ion channels become localized to distinct subcellular domains in the neuron. Specific targeting, clustering, and maintenance of these channels in their respective domains are essential to achieve high conduction velocities of action potential propagation.

nodes.name: clustering of voltage-gated potassium channels
nodes.description: The process in which voltage-gated potassium channels become localized together in high densities. In animals, voltage-gated potassium (Kv) channels are clustered beneath the myelin sheath in regions immediately adjacent to paranodes, called juxtaparanodes, and along the inner mesaxon within the internode.

nodes.name: organelle organization
nodes.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle within a cell. An organelle is an organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane.

nodes.name: cytoskeleton organization
nodes.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures.

nodes.name: mitochondrion organization
nodes.description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a mitochondrion; includes mitochondrial morphogenesis and distribution, and replication of the mitochondrial genome as well as synthesis of new mitochondrial components.

nodes.name: apoptotic mitochondrial changes
nodes.description: The morphological and physiological alterations undergone by mitochondria during apoptosis.

nodes.name: release of cytochrome c from mitochondria
nodes.description: The process that results in the movement of cytochrome c from the mitochondrial intermembrane space into the cytosol, which is part of the apoptotic signaling pathway and leads to caspase activation.

nodes.name: cellular metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

nodes.name: cellular macromolecule metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass, as carried out by individual cells.

nodes.name: cellular protein metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a specific protein, rather than of proteins in general, occurring at the level of an individual cell. Includes cellular protein modification.

nodes.name: cellular protein modification process
nodes.description: The covalent alteration of one or more amino acids occurring in proteins, peptides and nascent polypeptides (co-translational, post-translational modifications) occurring at the level of an individual cell. Includes the modification of charged tRNAs that are destined to occur in a protein (pre-translation modification).

nodes.name: peptidyl-amino acid modification
nodes.description: The alteration of an amino acid residue in a peptide.

nodes.name: peptidyl-lysine modification
nodes.description: The modification of peptidyl-lysine.

nodes.name: peptidyl-lysine desuccinylation
nodes.description: The removal of a succinyl group (CO-CH2-CH2-CO) from a succinylated lysine residue in a peptide or protein.

nodes.name: protein sumoylation
nodes.description: The process in which a SUMO protein (small ubiquitin-related modifier) is conjugated to a target protein via an isopeptide bond between the carboxyl terminus of SUMO with an epsilon-amino group of a lysine residue of the target protein.

nodes.name: protein dephosphorylation
nodes.description: The process of removing one or more phosphoric residues from a protein.

nodes.name: histone dephosphorylation
nodes.description: The modification of histones by removal of phosphate groups.

nodes.name: protein modification by small protein conjugation or removal
nodes.description: A protein modification process in which one or more groups of a small protein, such as ubiquitin or a ubiquitin-like protein, are covalently attached to or removed from a target protein.

nodes.name: protein modification by small protein conjugation
nodes.description: A protein modification process in which one or more groups of a small protein, such as ubiquitin or a ubiquitin-like protein, are covalently attached to a target protein.

nodes.name: protein ubiquitination
nodes.description: The process in which one or more ubiquitin groups are added to a protein.

nodes.name: DNA metabolic process
nodes.description: Any cellular metabolic process involving deoxyribonucleic acid. This is one of the two main types of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from one, or more commonly, two, strands of linked deoxyribonucleotides.

nodes.name: DNA double-strand break processing
nodes.description: The 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang.

nodes.name: DNA modification
nodes.description: The covalent alteration of one or more nucleotide sites in DNA, resulting in a change in its properties.

nodes.name: DNA deamination
nodes.description: The removal of an amino group from a nucleotide base in DNA. An example is the deamination of cytosine to produce uracil.

nodes.name: DNA cytosine deamination
nodes.description: The removal of an amino group from a cytosine residue in DNA, forming a uracil residue.

nodes.name: RNA metabolic process
nodes.description: The cellular chemical reactions and pathways involving RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3',5'-phosphodiester linkage.

nodes.name: mRNA metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving mRNA, messenger RNA, which is responsible for carrying the coded genetic 'message', transcribed from DNA, to sites of protein assembly at the ribosomes.

nodes.name: mRNA processing
nodes.description: Any process involved in the conversion of a primary mRNA transcript into one or more mature mRNA(s) prior to translation into polypeptide.

nodes.name: RNA polyadenylation
nodes.description: The enzymatic addition of a sequence of adenylyl residues at the 3' end of an RNA molecule.

nodes.name: mRNA polyadenylation
nodes.description: The enzymatic addition of a sequence of 40-200 adenylyl residues at the 3' end of a eukaryotic mRNA primary transcript.

nodes.name: cofactor metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a cofactor, a substance that is required for the activity of an enzyme or other protein. Cofactors may be inorganic, such as the metal atoms zinc, iron, and copper in certain forms, or organic, in which case they are referred to as coenzymes. Cofactors may either be bound tightly to active sites or bind loosely with the substrate.

nodes.name: coenzyme metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving coenzymes, any of various nonprotein organic cofactors that are required, in addition to an enzyme and a substrate, for an enzymatic reaction to proceed.

nodes.name: cofactor biosynthetic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a cofactor, a substance that is required for the activity of an enzyme or other protein.

nodes.name: siderophore biosynthetic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of siderophores, low molecular weight Fe(III)-chelating substances made by aerobic or facultatively anaerobic bacteria, especially when growing under iron deficient conditions. The complexes of Fe(3+)-siderophores have very high stability constants and are taken up by specific transport systems by microorganisms; the subsequent release of iron requires enzymatic action.

nodes.name: pyoverdine biosynthetic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of the siderochrome pyoverdine.

nodes.name: drug metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a drug, a substance used in the diagnosis, treatment or prevention of a disease; as used here antibiotic substances (see antibiotic metabolism) are considered to be drugs, even if not used in medical or veterinary practice.

nodes.name: antibiotic metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an antibiotic, a substance produced by or derived from certain fungi, bacteria, and other organisms, that can destroy or inhibit the growth of other microorganisms.

nodes.name: beta-lactam antibiotic metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a beta-lactam antibiotic, any member of a class of natural or semisynthetic antibiotics whose characteristic feature is a strained, four-membered beta-lactam ring. They include the penicillins and many of the cephalosporins.

nodes.name: organic acid metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

nodes.name: oxoacid metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any oxoacid; an oxoacid is a compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

nodes.name: carboxylic acid metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one or more carboxyl (COOH) groups or anions (COO-).

nodes.name: monocarboxylic acid metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (COOH) group or anion (COO-).

nodes.name: fatty acid metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving fatty acids, aliphatic monocarboxylic acids liberated from naturally occurring fats and oils by hydrolysis.

nodes.name: fatty acid oxidation
nodes.description: The removal of one or more electrons from a fatty acid, with or without the concomitant removal of a proton or protons, by reaction with an electron-accepting substance, by addition of oxygen or by removal of hydrogen.

nodes.name: pyruvate metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving pyruvate, 2-oxopropanoate.

nodes.name: glycolytic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a carbohydrate into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP and the reduction of NAD(P) to NAD(P)H. Glycolysis begins with the metabolism of a carbohydrate to generate products that can enter the pathway and ends with the production of pyruvate. Pyruvate may be converted to acetyl-coenzyme A, ethanol, lactate, or other small molecules.

nodes.name: glycolytic process through fructose-6-phosphate
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a monosaccharide into pyruvate, occurring through a fructose-6-phosphate intermediate, with the concomitant production of ATP and NADH.

nodes.name: phosphorus metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the nonmetallic element phosphorus or compounds that contain phosphorus, usually in the form of a phosphate group (PO4).

nodes.name: phosphate-containing compound metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the phosphate group, the anion or salt of any phosphoric acid.

nodes.name: dephosphorylation
nodes.description: The process of removing one or more phosphoric (ester or anhydride) residues from a molecule.

nodes.name: glucose 6-phosphate metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving glucose 6-phosphate, a monophosphorylated derivative of glucose with the phosphate group attached to C-6.

nodes.name: translational initiation
nodes.description: The process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein. This includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.

nodes.name: xenobiotic metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a xenobiotic compound, a compound foreign to living organisms. Used of chemical compounds, e.g. a xenobiotic chemical, such as a pesticide.

nodes.name: xenobiotic catabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a xenobiotic compound, a compound foreign to living organisms. Used of chemical compounds, e.g. a xenobiotic chemical, such as a pesticide.

nodes.name: cellular response to stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus by a cell and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell.

nodes.name: cellular response to biotic stimulus
nodes.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a biotic stimulus, a stimulus caused or produced by a living organism.

nodes.name: cellular response to molecule of bacterial origin
nodes.description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus by molecules of bacterial origin such as peptides derived from bacterial flagellin.

nodes.name: protein folding
nodes.description: The process of assisting in the covalent and noncovalent assembly of single chain polypeptides or multisubunit complexes into the correct tertiary structure.

nodes.name: single-organism cellular process
nodes.description: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, occurring within a single organism.

nodes.name: cell cycle process
nodes.description: The cellular process that ensures successive accurate and complete genome replication and chromosome segregation.

nodes.name: cell cycle checkpoint
nodes.description: A cell cycle process that controls cell cycle progression by monitoring the integrity of specific cell cycle events. A cell cycle checkpoint begins with detection of deficiencies or defects and ends with signal transduction.

nodes.name: ensheathment of neurons
nodes.description: The process in which glial cells envelop neuronal cell bodies and/or axons to form an insulating layer. This can take the form of myelinating or non-myelinating ensheathment.

nodes.name: axon ensheathment
nodes.description: Any process in which the axon of a neuron is insulated, and that insulation maintained, thereby preventing dispersion of the electrical signal.

nodes.name: peripheral nervous system axon ensheathment
nodes.description: The process in which a Schwann cell membrane closes around an axon in the peripheral nervous system. This can be a myelinating or a non-myelinating neuron-glial interaction.

nodes.name: myelination in peripheral nervous system
nodes.description: The process in which neuronal axons and dendrites become coated with a segmented lipid-rich sheath (myelin) to enable faster and more energetically efficient conduction of electrical impulses. The sheath is formed by the cell membranes of Schwann cells in the peripheral nervous system. Adjacent myelin segments are separated by a non-myelinated stretch of axon called a node of Ranvier.

nodes.name: one-carbon metabolic process
nodes.description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the transfer of one-carbon units in various oxidation states.
